00:30:11,060 --> 00:30:12,500
咱们得让Neal撤出来
We need to pull Neal out of there.

734
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:14,300
等等 Khatri博士应该有一份那个蛋的CT扫描图
Wait, Dr. Khatri should have a CAT scan of the egg.

735
00:30:14,360 --> 00:30:17,430
我联系她看看能不能发一份过来
I'll call to see if she can send one to us.

736
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:23,660
听说过马克胡特吗?
You ever heard of a Macuahuitl?

737
00:30:23,730 --> 00:30:26,760
不就是你手上正拿着的这件武器嘛
It's the weapon you're holding in your hands right now.

738
00:30:26,830 --> 00:30:30,600
John 关于这件武器 你还知道什么呢?
What else can you tell me about this weapon, John?

739
00:30:30,660 --> 00:30:34,200
特别是你面前这一件?
Anything about this one in particular?

740
00:30:34,260 --> 00:30:36,430
八年前我跟Holt在纽约
I stole it for you eight years ago

741
00:30:36,500 --> 00:30:38,960
合力为你偷来的
with Holt right here in New York.

742
00:30:39,030 --> 00:30:42,130
而且你拿的姿势不对
You're holding it wrong.

743
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:46,460
不介意吧?
You mind?

744
00:30:46,530 --> 00:30:50,460
早期的马克胡特在手柄顶端要宽两英寸
The early Macuahuitl handle is 2 inches wider at the top.

745
00:30:50,530 --> 00:30:51,900
要这样拿
Hold it like this.

746
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:54,230
握得越紧 挥动越迅速
Better grip means a faster swing.

747
00:30:54,300 --> 00:30:55,930
更好把控
More control.

748
00:31:03,630 --> 00:31:06,360
你的建议不错
You're right.

749
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:09,630
说起来 我也偷过不少东西
You know, I've stolen a lot of things,

750
00:31:09,700 --> 00:31:13,900
但极少是纯粹为了拥有而下手的
but I've rarely taken anything just to have it.

751
00:31:13,960 --> 00:31:16,230
有朝一日值得一试
You should try it sometime.

752
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:24,500
马上就要扫到胚胎那里了
We should be at the embryo any moment now.

753
00:31:30,330 --> 00:31:32,460
什么事?
Yeah?

754
00:31:32,530 --> 00:31:34,800
他来这干什么?
Why is he here?

755
00:31:34,860 --> 00:31:35,930
好吧
Fine.

756
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:38,300
我马上就到
I'll be right there.

757
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:40,860
谁来了?
Who's here?

758
00:31:40,930 --> 00:31:45,530
那个联邦调查局探员 还不死心呢
That FBI agent. Still shaking his trees.

759
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:47,800
别担心 我来搞定他
Don't worry, I'll get rid of him.

760
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:58,400
Forsythe先生 多谢赏脸
Mr. Forsythe, thanks for seeing me.

761
00:31:58,460 --> 00:32:01,430
我不会占用您太多时间
I won't take up much of your time.

762
00:32:01,500 --> 00:32:03,260
这是Michael Holt 他是我们
Michael Holt, he's our prime suspect

763
00:32:03,330 --> 00:32:05,230
在化石窃案中的主要嫌疑人
in the fossil shipment theft.

764
00:32:05,300 --> 00:32:06,760
这跟我有什么关系?
What's it got to do with me?

765
00:32:06,830 --> 00:32:09,330
我只是在想 他或许会来向您兜售
I was wondering if maybe he approached you on buying them.

766
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:16,460
这样啊 只要他联系我 我第一个告知你
Well, if he contacts me, you'll be my first call.

767
00:32:16,530 --> 00:32:18,430
就等着您这句话呢
All I wanted to hear.

768
00:32:18,500 --> 00:32:20,230
那就慢走不送了
Then you'll be on your way.

769
00:32:22,730 --> 00:32:26,700
说起来 虽然迅猛龙的名字意思是"快手贼"
You know, even though their name means "speedy thief",

770
00:32:26,760 --> 00:32:30,500
但它们的速度其实并没那么快
they say that the velociraptor wasn't particularly fast.

771
00:32:30,560 --> 00:32:31,700
的确如此
That's true.

772
00:32:31,760 --> 00:32:33,930
而且也不聪明
And that it was dumb.

773
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:36,600
我猜大脑的容量也不大
Yeah, not much room for a brain in there, I guess.

774
00:32:36,660 --> 00:32:40,730
不过是一只迟缓 迟钝 长着巨齿的大鸡
One slow, dumb chicken with big teeth.

775
00:32:40,800 --> 00:32:42,700
别碰那个头骨
Don't touch the skull.

776
00:32:42,760 --> 00:32:44,600
这些牙齿您是怎么粘起来的?
How do you keep them glued in there?

777
00:32:44,660 --> 00:32:46,330
环氧树脂还是廉价胶?
Epoxy or tacky?

778
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:48,430
Burke探员 别...
Agent Burke, don't...

779
00:32:50,030 --> 00:32:53,600
看来你该用强力胶的
Guess you should've used superglue.

780
00:32:53,660 --> 00:32:55,900
- 玩够了吗?  - 嗯
- Is that all?  - Mm-hmm.

781
00:33:03,330 --> 00:33:06,400
抱歉弄坏了你的恐龙
Sorry I broke your dinosaur.

782
00:33:13,830 --> 00:33:16,660
快看看
Well, will you look at that?

783
00:33:22,460 --> 00:33:25,060
钱在公文包里
Money's in the briefcase.

784
00:33:27,130 --> 00:33:30,500
很荣幸跟你做生意
Pleasure doing business with you.

785
00:33:53,400 --> 00:33:56,160
趁着没人做的那些见不得人的事
The things people do when they think no one's watching.

786
00:33:56,230 --> 00:33:58,060
就好比跟踪自己的朋友
Like following your friend to a first date

787
00:33:58,130 --> 00:33:59,330
毁了他的首次约会?
and crashing it?

788
00:33:59,400 --> 00:34:01,860
走吧
Come on.

789
00:34:01,930 --> 00:34:05,260
让Forsythe见识见识联邦调查局是怎么看待自然选择的
Let's show Forsythe how the FBI handles natural selection.

790
00:34:05,330 --> 00:34:06,360
就憋出这么一句?
You just think of that one?

791
00:34:06,430 --> 00:34:08,330
嗯 出动吧
Yeah, on the way over.

792
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:21,760
你在这干什么?
What the hell are you doing here?

793
00:34:21,830 --> 00:34:23,760
我想了想你说的话
I thought about what you said.

794
00:34:23,830 --> 00:34:26,800
我想清楚了自己想要什么
I figured out what I wanna take.

795
00:34:29,460 --> 00:34:31,260
你怎么跟我到这来的?
How'd you follow me?

796
00:34:31,330 --> 00:34:33,760
那个小家伙告诉我的
That little guy told me where you were.

797
00:34:33,830 --> 00:34:37,360
或者至少可以说是里面那个GPS追踪器的功劳
Or at least a GPS tracker we put inside it did.

798
00:34:42,330 --> 00:34:44,500
走吧
Let's go.

799
00:34:49,660 --> 00:34:50,830
打开
Open it up.

800
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:10,430
这是当真俘获了我的想象力
Okay, that definitely captures my imagination.

801
00:35:18,900 --> 00:35:21,400
你想当古生物学家已经晚了
You know, it's not too late for you to be a paleontologist.

802
00:35:21,460 --> 00:35:23,460
有些东西远观即可 距离产生美
Some things are better enjoyed from a distance.

803
00:35:23,530 --> 00:35:25,430
正如大型盗窃案一般
Oh, like grand larceny.

804
00:35:25,500 --> 00:35:26,800
你就没点正当合法的兴趣爱好吗?
Are all of your hobbies illegal?

805
00:35:26,860 --> 00:35:28,160
国际象棋
I like chess.

806
00:35:28,230 --> 00:35:30,130
你曾在联合广场兜售国际象棋
You hustled chess in Union Square.

807
00:35:30,200 --> 00:35:31,260
Burke探员
Agent Burke.

808
00:35:31,330 --> 00:35:33,600
Caffrey先生 跟我来
Mr. Caffrey, follow me.

809
00:35:33,660 --> 00:35:35,030
你们得看看这个
You need to see this.

810
00:35:38,200 --> 00:35:40,430
这就是她
Here she is.

811
00:35:40,500 --> 00:35:41,900
她真是...
She's...

812
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:45,200
雄伟
majestic.

813
00:35:45,260 --> 00:35:46,830
正因为你们俩
This mother and child reunion

814
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:48,630
这对母子才得以重聚
was only possible because of you two.

815
00:35:48,700 --> 00:35:50,560
博物馆方面欠您一份人情
The museum is in your debt.

816
00:35:50,630 --> 00:35:54,100
我倒是知道有人想要个全年免票
I know someone who would love a year-round pass.

817
00:35:54,160 --> 00:35:57,330
Burke探员 您在我们这边有VIP资格
Agent Burke, you have VIP status here.

818
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:59,560
我们的大门一直向您敞开
Our doors are always open.

819
00:35:59,630 --> 00:36:01,200
Peter Burke 你可是VIP啊 我们得给你搞个徽章
Peter Burke, VIP. We should get you a badge.

820
00:36:01,260 --> 00:36:03,460
低调点 谢谢你 博士
Quiet. Thank you, Doctor.

821
00:36:03,530 --> 00:36:07,330
谢谢你
Thank you.

822
00:36:07,400 --> 00:36:09,000
今晚来我家吃晚饭
Come by the house for dinner tonight.

823
00:36:09,060 --> 00:36:10,600
El要做柠檬鲈鱼
El's cooking branzino.

824
00:36:10,660 --> 00:36:12,600
柠檬鲈鱼 瞧瞧你多滋润
Branzino, look at you.

825
00:36:12,660 --> 00:36:13,960
我的生活也可以很炫的
I can be fancy.

826
00:36:14,030 --> 00:36:14,930
多谢邀请 但...
Thanks for the invitation, but...

827
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:16,400
不是邀请
It's not an invitation.

828
00:36:16,460 --> 00:36:17,400
看来是命令了?
So it's an order?

829
00:36:17,460 --> 00:36:18,960
晚上七点
7:00 p.m.

830
00:36:19,030 --> 00:36:21,460
别迟到了 Caffrey探员
Don't be late, Agent Caffrey.

831
00:36:31,300 --> 00:36:33,860
真是糟糕
Bad news.

832
00:36:33,930 --> 00:36:36,560
又是一顿佳肴
Another amazing meal.

833
00:36:36,630 --> 00:36:37,700
必须的 这可是出自你手
Well, it should be. It's your recipe.

834
00:36:37,760 --> 00:36:39,160
当初应该在烧烤时露一手的
Should've thrown it on a barbecue.

835
00:36:39,230 --> 00:36:41,000
千万别让他当副主厨
Never let him be sous chef.

836
00:36:41,060 --> 00:36:44,030
其实他还是挺擅长烧烤的
He's actually very good on the barbecue.

837
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:48,600
好吧... Rebecca
So... Rebecca.

838
00:36:48,660 --> 00:36:51,100
- 没错 Rebecca  - 你们想听什么?
- Yeah, Rebecca.  - What do you wanna know?

839
00:36:51,160 --> 00:36:53,160
你告诉她一切了吗?
Have you told her everything?

840
00:36:53,230 --> 00:36:55,130
一切?
Everything?

841
00:36:55,200 --> 00:36:56,500
你为什么为联邦调查局工作?
Why you're working for the FBI?

842
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:57,930
- 你为什么戴着脚链?  - 她看到过吗?
- Why you're wearing an anklet?  - Has she seen it?

843
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:01,700
好吧 我只是在等待合适的时机
Okay, I was waiting for the right time.

844
00:37:01,760 --> 00:37:03,660
不存在什么合适的时机 Neal
There's no right time, Neal.

845
00:37:03,730 --> 00:37:05,960
如果我告诉她真相 你们觉得会怎么样?
What do you think happens if I tell her the truth?

846
00:37:06,030 --> 00:37:08,160
时间拖得越久
The more time passes,

847
00:37:08,230 --> 00:37:10,100
真相便越伤人
the more the truth will hurt.

848
00:37:10,160 --> 00:37:12,530
如果你对她是真心的
If you really want this to work,

849
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:14,830
现在就告诉她
tell her now.

850
00:37:14,900 --> 00:37:18,100
祈祷她会接受你
Pray she'll accept it.

851
00:37:18,160 --> 00:37:19,200
你也这么觉得?
You agree?

852
00:37:19,260 --> 00:37:21,160
如果你真的在乎Rebecca
If you really care about Rebecca,

853
00:37:21,230 --> 00:37:23,200
她就有权了解真正的你
she deserves to know the real you.

854
00:37:23,260 --> 00:37:26,360
好吧 那假如当初Peter跟你相识之初
Okay, if Peter had told you something like this

855
00:37:26,430 --> 00:37:29,600
向你坦白了类似的情况 你会接受他吗?
when you first met, would you have accepted it?

856
00:37:31,730 --> 00:37:34,700
老实说 Neal 我... 我不知道
Honestly, Neal, I... I don't know.

857
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:36,730
但我会希望选择是我自己做出的
But I'd want the choice to decide.

858
00:37:36,800 --> 00:37:39,400
我相信Rebecca也同样如此
And so will Rebecca.

859
00:37:39,460 --> 00:37:42,400
这个险你不得不冒
It's a risk you should take.

860
00:37:52,760 --> 00:37:55,560
我简直不想问你这玩意是怎么搞来的
I don't wanna ask why you have that thing.

861
00:37:55,630 --> 00:37:58,300
就在那儿 不拿白不拿
Mm, it was there for the taking.

862
00:37:58,360 --> 00:38:00,330
谢了
Thank you.

863
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:02,360
别客气 干杯
You're welcome. Cheers.

864
00:38:02,430 --> 00:38:04,330
- 干杯  - 嗯
- Cheers.  - Mmm.

865
00:38:06,630 --> 00:38:10,330
Byron以前一直说这座城市会跟他对话
Byron always said the city spoke to him.

866
00:38:10,400 --> 00:38:11,960
可以想见
I can relate to that.

867
00:38:12,030 --> 00:38:14,460
你很像他
You're a lot like him.

868
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:19,200
他告诉你他是个罪犯的时候 你作何感想?
How did you feel when he told you he was a criminal?

869
00:38:21,530 --> 00:38:23,530
很心痛
It hurt.

870
00:38:23,600 --> 00:38:25,860
但我依然爱他
But I loved him.

871
00:38:25,930 --> 00:38:28,800
他做过什么并不重要
And it didn't matter what he was.

872
00:38:28,860 --> 00:38:31,200
重要的是他是什么样的人
It only mattered who he was.

873
00:38:34,260 --> 00:38:36,400
我也希望我能将这二者区分
I wish I could separate the two.

874
00:38:36,460 --> 00:38:39,730
时间会给你答案的
Well, you'll learn with time.

875
00:38:46,500 --> 00:38:48,400
等一下
Just a second.

876
00:38:55,530 --> 00:38:58,030
嘿 有新发现了?
Hey. Find something new?

877
00:38:58,100 --> 00:39:00,430
- 嗯  - 太棒了
- Yeah.  - Great.

878
00:39:03,430 --> 00:39:04,660
其实没有
No.

879
00:39:04,730 --> 00:39:07,900
我是想假装发现了什么
I was gonna lie, pretend I found something,

880
00:39:07,960 --> 00:39:12,560
但我只是想来看看你
but I just wanted to come see you.

881
00:39:12,630 --> 00:39:14,760
无论现在我们之间算是什么关系
Whatever this is between us,

882
00:39:14,830 --> 00:39:18,200
我... 我都不想停下来
I... I don't want it to stop.

883
00:39:18,260 --> 00:39:21,260
我也不想
I don't either.

884
00:39:21,330 --> 00:39:22,760
是吗?
Yeah?

885
00:39:22,830 --> 00:39:26,130
但有件事你应该先知道
But there's something you should know about me.

886
00:39:26,200 --> 00:39:27,860
好的
Okay.

887
00:39:36,630 --> 00:39:40,530
我不是联邦调查局探员
I'm not an FBI agent.

888
00:39:40,600 --> 00:39:43,060
我是个罪犯线人
I'm a criminal informant.

889
00:39:43,130 --> 00:39:45,130
我因伪造债券被定罪
I was convicted of bond forgery

890
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:48,330
在成为罪犯线人之前
and served part of a four-year sentence

891
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:51,360
服过四年刑期的一部分
before I became a CI.

892
00:39:51,430 --> 00:39:53,000
我... 我没明白
I'm... I don't understand.

893
00:39:53,060 --> 00:39:54,460
我去过你的办公室
I've been to your office.

894
00:39:54,530 --> 00:39:57,230
我一直与你的上司Gruetzner探员合作
I've been working with your boss, Agent Gruetzner.

895
00:39:57,300 --> 00:39:58,660
他不是我的上司
Yeah, he's not my boss.

896
00:39:58,760 --> 00:40:00,960
我真正的上司是Peter Burke 那天晚餐遇见的那位
My real boss is Peter Burke, who you met at dinner.

897
00:40:01,030 --> 00:40:05,230
那个办公室只是事先布置好
That office was just a setup

898
00:40:05,300 --> 00:40:08,660
为了让你帮忙破解法典的
to get your help with the codex.

899
00:40:08,730 --> 00:40:12,660
你布置了一间假办公室以便向我撒谎?
You set up a fake office all so you could lie to me?

900
00:40:12,730 --> 00:40:13,860
你到底是不是在研究法典啊?
Are you even researching the codex?

901
00:40:13,930 --> 00:40:15,260
是的
I am.

902
00:40:15,330 --> 00:40:18,260
只不过不是为联邦调查局调查
Just not for the FBI.

903
00:40:21,360 --> 00:40:22,830
Rebecca啊
Rebecca.

904
00:40:22,900 --> 00:40:24,900
你为什么这样对我?
Why would you do this to me?

905
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:26,930
我需要你的帮助
I needed your help, all right?

906
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:28,560
而我...
And I...

907
00:40:28,630 --> 00:40:31,200
我没想到这件事
I didn't expect this.

908
00:40:31,260 --> 00:40:33,900
我没想到我们会有进展
I didn't expect us.

909
00:40:40,360 --> 00:40:42,960
还有什么别的瞒着我的吗?
Is there anything else I should know?

910
00:41:22,860 --> 00:41:23,800
谢谢
Thank you.

911
00:41:23,860 --> 00:41:25,430
我想我...
I think I was just...

912
00:41:25,500 --> 00:41:26,960
June啊!
June!

913
00:41:27,030 --> 00:41:28,760
是Neal啊!
Neal!

914
00:41:28,830 --> 00:41:31,100
我刚才在和这位出色的男士聊天
I was just chatting with this wonderful man,

915
00:41:31,160 --> 00:41:32,130
叫...
Mr...

916
00:41:32,200 --> 00:41:33,760
叫我Curtis就好
You can call me "Curtis".

917
00:41:33,830 --> 00:41:35,600
Curtis 好可爱的名字
Curtis. It's a lovely name.

918
00:41:35,660 --> 00:41:37,030
谢谢
Thank you.

919
00:41:37,100 --> 00:41:39,700
那...
Well, I think...

920
00:41:39,760 --> 00:41:42,600
我就先走了
I'll just be running along.

921
00:41:44,860 --> 00:41:46,760
Hagen 离她远点
You stay away from her, Hagen.

922
00:41:46,830 --> 00:41:49,000
